7 An Act relating to public finance; enacting the
Oklahoma Common Cents Act; providing for system of
8 rounding with respect to certain cash payments;
prescribing method for rounding; providing for
9 permissive computations; prescribing date for
mandatory computations; providing for exclusion of
10 certain transactions; providing for payment of
certain shortages; authorizing certain actions by
11 political subdivisions; requiring entities of this
state and certain entities to round the price of
12 certain transactions paid with cash; prescribing
procedure for rounding; providing for exclusion of
13 certain transactions; providing for noncodification;
providing for codification; providing an effective
14 date; and declaring an emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
19 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
20 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma Common
21 Cents Act".
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9002 of Title 62, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3075 Page 1

1 A. Unless actions by the United States Congress direct
2 otherwise, from the effective date of this act until July 1, 2027,
3 any political subdivision may round final amounts owed to the entity
4 as follows if the payment is made in the form of cash so that an
5 amount ending in:
6 1. One cent ($0.01) or two cents ($0.02) is rounded down to
7 zero (0);
8 2. Three cents ($0.03) or four cents ($0.04) is rounded up to
9 five cents ($0.05);
10 3. Six cents ($0.06) or seven cents ($0.07) is rounded down to
11 five cents ($0.05); and
12 4. Eight cents ($0.08) or nine cents ($0.09) is rounded up to
13 ten cents ($0.10).
14 B. The provisions of subsection A of this section shall be
15 mandatory beginning July 1, 2027.
16 C. The provisions of this section shall not apply to any
17 payment method such as a check, debit card, credit card, electronic
18 or digital payment, or other similar form of payment, but shall only
19 apply to payments made using cash or the portion paid in cash.
20 D. For payment of ad valorem taxes, the overage or underage of
21 cash payments shall be accounted for from the county's portion of
22 the unappropriated revenue for the general fund.
23
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3075 Page 2

1 E. Any political subdivision of the state may account for any
2 over or under cash payments from a fund under its control as
3 determined by the governing body of the political subdivision.
4 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3120 of Title 74, unless there
6 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 A. For any agency, constitutionally or statutorily created
8 state board, bureau, commission, office, authority, public trust in
9 which the state is a beneficiary, or interstate commission accepting
10 cash as payment from an individual, such entity shall adjust the
11 price, fee, penalty, or any other charge, excluding the payment of
12 any tax levy, by rounding the total amount of the transaction as
13 provided by subsection B of this section.
14 B. Final amounts owed to the entity shall be rounded as follows
15 if the payment is made in the form of cash so that an amount ending
16 in:
17 1. One cent ($0.01) or two cents ($0.02) is rounded down to
18 zero (0);
19 2. Three cents ($0.03) or four cents ($0.04) is rounded up to
20 five cents ($0.05);
21 3. Six cents ($0.06) or seven cents ($0.07) is rounded down to
22 five cents ($0.05); and
23 4. Eight cents ($0.08) or nine cents ($0.09) is rounded up to
24 ten cents ($0.10).
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3075 Page 3

1 C. The provisions of this section shall not apply to any
2 payment method such as a check, debit card, credit card, electronic
3 or digital payment, or other similar form of payment, but shall only
4 apply to payments made using cash or the portion paid in cash.
5 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
6 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
7 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
8 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
9 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
10 Passed the House of Representatives the 24th day of March, 2026.
